               <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
               <faith type="EOTC"/>
               <occupation type="ecclesiastic">abbot</occupation>
               <birth when="1613"/>
               <floruit notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699">He was a monk during the contemporary of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                  <persName ref="PRS4015Fasilada">Fāsiladas</persName> and credited with  the foundation of 
                  the monastery bearing his name in the district of <placeName ref="LOC1292Ahsaa">ʾAhsaʾa</placeName>
                . In his youth time, he was frequently in the court of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS4015Fasilada">Fāsiladas</persName>, where the king offered him his daughter. However, he chose to take  a monastic habit from 
                  <persName ref="PRS8751senaKre">Śǝna Krǝstos</persName>. As  a result, he was much desliked by his relative and he then settled in 
                  <placeName ref="LOC6171Waldeb">Wāldǝbbā</placeName> from where he made various sancturies. He is reported to have converted pagans at lake 
                  <placeName ref="LOC1017AbbaNa">ʾAbbā Nāza</placeName>.</floruit>             
               <death when="1706"> He died at the age of 93. </death>
            </person>
